{"title_page": "H\u00e4selgehr", "text_new": "'''H\u00e4selgehr''' is a municipality with 686 inhabitants (as of 1 January 2019) in the district of [[Reutte (district)|Reutte]] in the [[Austria]]n state of [[state of Tyrol|Tyrol]]. The municipality is located in the district court Reutte. Since 2010, the community is a member of the Climate Alliance Tyrol.{{Infobox settlement\n| name            = H\u00e4selgehr\n| native_name     = \n| settlement_type = \n<!-- Images     -->\n| image_skyline   = Haeselgehr01.JPG\n| imagesize       = \n| image_caption   = \n| image_shield    = Wappen at haeselgehr.png\n| shield_size     = 80x110px\n| shield_link     = \n<!-- Maps           -->\n| pushpin_map         = Austria\n| pushpin_mapsize     = 270\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location within Austria\n| image_map           = \n| mapsize             = \n| map_alt             =\n| map_caption         = Location within Reutte district\n<!-- Location    -->\n| coordinates       = {{coord|47|18|30|N|10|29|30|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type  = Country\n| subdivision_name  = [[Austria]]\n| subdivision_type1 = [[States of Austria|State]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Tyrol (state)|Tyrol]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[District (Austria)|District]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[Reutte District|Reutte]]\n| parts_type        = \n| parts_style       = para\n| p1                = \n<!-- Leaders -->\n| leader_title  = [[Burgomaster|Mayor]]\n| leader_name   = Harald Friedle\n| leader_party  = \n| leader_title1 = \n| leader_name1  = \n<!-- Statistics -->\n| area_footnotes   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_footnotes}}\n| area_total_km2   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_total_km2}}\n| area_metro_km2   = \n| elevation_m      = 1006\n| elevation_max_m  = \n| elevation_min_m  = \n| population_as_of = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_as_of}}\n| population_footnotes = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_footnotes}}\n| population_total = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_total}}\n| population_urban =  \n| population_metro =  \n| population_note  = \n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| established_title = \n| established_date  = \n| timezone          = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| timezone_DST      = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset        = +1\n| utc_offset_DST    = +2\n| registration_plate = [[Vehicle registration plates of Austria|RE]]\n| postal_code_type   = [[List of postal codes in Austria|Postal code]]\n| postal_code        = 6651\n| area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Austria|Area code]]\n| area_code      = 05634\n| website   = [http://www.haeselgehr.tirol.gv.at www.haeselgehr.<br>tirol.gv.at]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n==Geography==\nH\u00e4selgher lies in the upper valley of the [[Lech (river)|Lech]] and consists of several loosely populated hamlets. The place was first documented in 1358 as Hesligeren (\"hazel-covered mites\" - wedge-shaped corridor). Heuberg near H\u00e4selgehr, which was cultivated to the ridge with mountain mowers, has often been the cause of [[Avalanche|avalanche disasters]] in the past, which is why the community is today protected by one of the largest avalanche barriers in Central Europe. In H\u00e4selgehr, the road branches off to [[Gramais]], the smallest municipality in Austria, which is seven kilometers away.\n\n== Constituent communities ==\nThe municipal area comprises the following two villages (population as of 1 January 2019<ref>{{cite web|title=H\u00e4selgehr|periodical=|publisher=|url=https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/H%C3%A4selgehr|url-status=|format=|access-date=2019-11-22|archive-url=|archive-date=|last=Wikipedia:de|date=|year=|language=|pages=|quote=}}</ref>{{Circular reference|date=January 2020}}):\n\n Grie\u00dfau (149)\n\n H\u00e4selgehr (537)\n\nDistricts of H\u00e4selgehr are Ober- and Untergrie\u00dfau, Ort, Sch\u00f6nau, Ober- and Unterh\u00e4selgehr, Unterh\u00f6f, Ebele, Luxnach, Alach, Rauchwand, H\u00e4ternach and Gutschau, neighboring communities [[Bach, Austria|Bach]], [[Elbigenalp]], [[Elmen]], [[Gramais]], [[Hinterhornbach]], [[Imst]] and [[Pfafflar]]\n\n[[File:H\u00e4selgehr, katholische Pfarrkirche heilige Martin Dm64094 foto4 2014-07-25 15.30.jpg|H\u00e4selgehr, church: katholische Pfarrkirche heilige Martin|thumb|240px|left]]\n[[File:Gutschau, woningen met bergen op achtergrond foto8 2014-07-25 15.147.jpg|Gutschau, living houses with mountains in background|thumb|center|250px]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n\n{{Cities and towns in Reutte (district)}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Haselgehr}}\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Reutte District]]\n\n\n{{Tyrol-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''H\u00e4selgehr''' is a municipality with 686 inhabitants (as of 1 January 2019) in the district of [[Reutte (district)|Reutte]] in the [[Austria]]n state of [[state of Tyrol|Tyrol]]. The municipality is located in the district court Reutte. Since 2010, the community is a member of the Climate Alliance Tyrol.{{Infobox settlement\n| name            = H\u00e4selgehr\n| native_name     = \n| settlement_type = \n<!-- Images     -->\n| image_skyline   = Haeselgehr01.JPG\n| imagesize       = \n| image_caption   = \n| image_shield    = Wappen at haeselgehr.png\n| shield_size     = 80x110px\n| shield_link     = \n<!-- Maps           -->\n| pushpin_map         = Austria\n| pushpin_mapsize     = 270\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location within Austria\n| image_map           = \n| mapsize             = \n| map_alt             =\n| map_caption         = Location within Reutte district\n<!-- Location    -->\n| coordinates       = {{coord|47|18|30|N|10|29|30|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type  = Country\n| subdivision_name  = [[Austria]]\n| subdivision_type1 = [[States of Austria|State]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Tyrol (state)|Tyrol]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[District (Austria)|District]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[Reutte District|Reutte]]\n| parts_type        = \n| parts_style       = para\n| p1                = \n<!-- Leaders -->\n| leader_title  = [[Burgomaster|Mayor]]\n| leader_name   = Harald Friedle\n| leader_party  = \n| leader_title1 = \n| leader_name1  = \n<!-- Statistics -->\n| area_footnotes   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_footnotes}}\n| area_total_km2   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_total_km2}}\n| area_metro_km2   = \n| elevation_m      = 1006\n| elevation_max_m  = \n| elevation_min_m  = \n| population_as_of = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_as_of}}\n| population_footnotes = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_footnotes}}\n| population_total = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_total}}\n| population_urban =  \n| population_metro =  \n| population_note  = \n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| established_title = \n| established_date  = \n| timezone          = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| timezone_DST      = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset        = +1\n| utc_offset_DST    = +2\n| registration_plate = [[Vehicle registration plates of Austria|RE]]\n| postal_code_type   = [[List of postal codes in Austria|Postal code]]\n| postal_code        = 6651\n| area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Austria|Area code]]\n| area_code      = 05634\n| website   = [http://www.haeselgehr.tirol.gv.at www.haeselgehr.<br>tirol.gv.at]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n==Geography==\nH\u00e4selgher lies in the upper valley of the [[Lech (river)|Lech]] and consists of several loosely populated hamlets. The place was first documented in 1358 as Hesligeren (\"hazel-covered mites\" - wedge-shaped corridor). Heuberg near H\u00e4selgehr, which was cultivated to the ridge with mountain mowers, has often been the cause of [[Avalanche|avalanche disasters]] in the past, which is why the community is today protected by one of the largest avalanche barriers in Central Europe. In H\u00e4selgehr, the road branches off to [[Gramais]], the smallest municipality in Austria, which is seven kilometers away.\n\n== Constituent communities ==\nThe municipal area comprises the following two villages (population as of 1 January 2019<ref>{{cite web|title=H\u00e4selgehr|periodical=|publisher=|url=https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/H%C3%A4selgehr|url-status=|format=|access-date=2019-11-22|archive-url=|archive-date=|last=Wikipedia:de|date=|year=|language=|pages=|quote=}}</ref>{{Circular reference|date=January 2020}}):\n\n Grie\u00dfau (149)\n\n H\u00e4selgehr (537)\n\nDistricts of H\u00e4selgehr are Ober- and Untergrie\u00dfau, Ort, Sch\u00f6nau, Ober- and Unterh\u00e4selgehr, Unterh\u00f6f, Ebele, Luxnach, Alach, Rauchwand, H\u00e4ternach and Gutschau, neighboring communities [[Bach, Austria|Bach]], [[Elbigenalp]], [[Elmen]], [[Gramais]], [[Hinterhornbach]], [[Imst]] and [[Pfafflar]]<br />\n\n[[File:H\u00e4selgehr, katholische Pfarrkirche heilige Martin Dm64094 foto4 2014-07-25 15.30.jpg|H\u00e4selgehr, church: katholische Pfarrkirche heilige Martin|thumb|240px|left]]\n[[File:Gutschau, woningen met bergen op achtergrond foto8 2014-07-25 15.147.jpg|Gutschau, living houses with mountains in background|thumb|center|250px]]\n\n<br />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commonscat}}\n\n{{Cities and towns in Reutte (district)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Haselgehr}}\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Reutte District]]\n\n\n{{Tyrol-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/H%C3%A4selgehr"}
{"title_page": "H\u00e1ss\u00e1gy", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| official_name                   = H\u00e1ss\u00e1gy\n| image_skyline                   = H\u00e1ss\u00e1gy,_Kossuth_utca_Olasz_fel\u0151l.jpg\n| image_shield                    = HUN H\u00e1ss\u00e1gy COA.jpg\n| pushpin_map                     = Hungary\n| pushpin_label_position          = <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location within [[Hungary]].\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|46|2|0|N|18|23|0|E|region:HU|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name                = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Regions of Hungary|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Southern Transdanubia]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Baranya County|Baranya]]\n| subdivision_type3               = [[Districts of Hungary|District]]\n| subdivision_name3               = [[B\u00f3ly District|B\u00f3ly]]\n| area_total_km2                  = 8\n| area_footnotes                  = <ref name=\"HunStats2018\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ksh.hu/apps/shop.kiadvany?p_kiadvany_id=1039140&p_lang=EN|title=Gazetteer of Hungary, 1st January 2018|publisher=Hungarian Central Statistical Office|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=4 June 2019}}</ref>\n| population_total                = 254\n| population_as_of                = 2018\n| population_footnotes            = <ref name=\"HunStats2018\" />\n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| timezone                        = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset                      = +1\n| timezone_DST                    = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST                  = +2\n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal code]]\n| postal_code                     = 7745\n| area_code                       = 69\n| geocode                         = 27881\n| name                            = \n| government_type                 = [[Mayor-council government]]\n| government_footnotes            = <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.valasztas.hu/dyn/onk14/szavossz/hu/M02/T090/tjk.html|title=Municipal Elections 2014|language=Hungarian|publisher=Hungarian National Election Office|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=5 June 2019}}</ref>\n| leader_title                    = [[Mayor]]\n| leader_party                    = Independent\n| leader_name                     = L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Lajos R\u00e1cz\n| website                         = {{URL|http://www.hassagy.hu/}}\n| settlement_type                 = Municipality\n| native_name                     = Haschad\n| native_name_lang                = de\n}}\n\n'''H\u00e1ss\u00e1gy''' ({{lang-hr|A\u0161a\u0111}}, {{lang-de|Haschad}}) is a [[village]] and [[Municipalities of Hungary|municipality]] ({{lang-hu|[[k\u00f6zs\u00e9g]]}}) in [[Baranya (county)|Baranya]] county, [[Hungary]].\n\n== Geography ==\nH\u00e1ss\u00e1gy is located on H\u00e1ss\u00e1gy Pond ({{lang-hu|H\u00e1ss\u00e1gyi-halast\u00f3}}) in [[Baranya County]], about seventeen kilometers southeast of [[P\u00e9cs]] and fifteen kilometers northwest of [[B\u00f3ly]]. It is about 20 kilometers west of the [[Danube]], 30 kilometers from [[Croatia]] and 50 kilometers from [[Serbia]]. The municipality lies within the [[Southern Transdanubia|Southern Transdanubia Region]] of Hungary. It previously was part of the [[Moh\u00e1cs Subregion]] but during the creation of districts in 2013, it became part of [[B\u00f3ly District]].\n\n== Demographics ==\nDuring the census of 2011, the population was 266. The vast majority of the population claimed [[Hungarians|Hungarian]] ethnicity (94.9%), though 45.6% also claimed [[Germans of Hungary|German]] ethnicity and the municipality has a [[National Self-Government of Germans in Hungary|German local minority self-government]]. Other ethnicities included [[Croats|Croatian]] (1.5%). 3.7% did not wish to answer. In terms of religious practice, 84.2% reported to be [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]], 4% [[Calvinism|Calvinist]], 5.5% of no religious affiliation and 4.8% did not wish to answer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ksh.hu/apps/hntr.telepules?p_lang=EN&p_id=27881|title=Detailed Gazetteer of Hungary|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Hungarian Central Statistical Office|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=5 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Transport ==\nThe closest railway station is in [[P\u00e9cs]], 16 kilometers to the northwest. The village lies near the [[M60 motorway (Hungary)|M60]] motorway, which opened in the area in 2010 and currently provides links west to [[P\u00e9cs]] and north to [[Budapest]] (via the [[M6 motorway (Hungary)|M6 motorway]]), and will eventually provide links to the [[Croatia]]n border at [[Iv\u00e1nd\u00e1rda]] and [[Barcs]].\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://portal.ksh.hu/pls/portal/cp.hnt_telep?NN=27881 Local statistics] {{in lang|hu}}\n\n{{Baranya}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hassagy}}\n[[Category:Populated places in Baranya County]]\n\n\n{{Baranya-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| official_name                   = H\u00e1ss\u00e1gy\n| image_skyline                   = H\u00e1ss\u00e1gy,_Kossuth_utca_Olasz_fel\u0151l.jpg\n| image_shield                    = HUN H\u00e1ss\u00e1gy COA.jpg\n| pushpin_map                     = Hungary\n| pushpin_label_position          = <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location within [[Hungary]].\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|46|2|0|N|18|23|0|E|region:HU|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name                = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Regions of Hungary|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Southern Transdanubia]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Baranya County|Baranya]]\n| subdivision_type3               = [[Districts of Hungary|District]]\n| subdivision_name3               = [[B\u00f3ly District|B\u00f3ly]]\n| area_total_km2                  = 8\n| area_footnotes                  = <ref name=\"HunStats2018\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ksh.hu/apps/shop.kiadvany?p_kiadvany_id=1039140&p_lang=EN|title=Gazetteer of Hungary, 1st January 2018|publisher=Hungarian Central Statistical Office|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=4 June 2019}}</ref>\n| population_total                = 254\n| population_as_of                = 2018\n| population_footnotes            = <ref name=\"HunStats2018\" />\n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| timezone                        = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset                      = +1\n| timezone_DST                    = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST                  = +2\n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal code]]\n| postal_code                     = 7745\n| area_code                       = 69\n| geocode                         = 27881\n| name                            = \n| government_type                 = [[Mayor-council government]]\n| government_footnotes            = <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.valasztas.hu/dyn/onk14/szavossz/hu/M02/T090/tjk.html|title=Municipal Elections 2014|language=Hungarian|publisher=Hungarian National Election Office|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=5 June 2019}}</ref>\n| leader_title                    = [[Mayor]]\n| leader_party                    = Independent\n| leader_name                     = L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Lajos R\u00e1cz\n| website                         = {{URL|http://www.hassagy.hu/}}\n| settlement_type                 = Municipality\n| native_name                     = Haschad\n| native_name_lang                = de\n}}\n\n'''H\u00e1ss\u00e1gy''' ({{lang-hr|A\u0161a\u0111}}, {{lang-de|Haschad}}) is a [[village]] and [[Municipalities of Hungary|municipality]] ({{lang-hu|[[k\u00f6zs\u00e9g]]}}) in [[Baranya (county)|Baranya]] county, [[Hungary]].\n\n== Geography ==\nH\u00e1ss\u00e1gy is located on H\u00e1ss\u00e1gy Pond ({{lang-hu|H\u00e1ss\u00e1gyi-halast\u00f3}}) in [[Baranya County]], about seventeen kilometers southeast of [[P\u00e9cs]] and fifteen kilometers northwest of [[B\u00f3ly]]. It is about 20 kilometers west of the [[Danube]], 30 kilometers from [[Croatia]] and 50 kilometers from [[Serbia]]. The municipality lies within the [[Southern Transdanubia|Southern Transdanubia Region]] of Hungary. It previously was part of the [[Moh\u00e1cs Subregion]] but during the creation of districts in 2013, it became part of [[B\u00f3ly District]].\n\n== Demographics ==\nDuring the census of 2011, the population was 266. The vast majority of the population claimed [[Hungarians|Hungarian]] ethnicity (94.9%), though 45.6% also claimed [[Germans of Hungary|German]] ethnicity and the municipality has a [[National Self-Government of Germans in Hungary|German local minority self-government]]. Other ethnicities included [[Croats|Croatian]] (1.5%). 3.7% did not wish to answer. In terms of religious practice, 84.2% reported to be [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]], 4% [[Calvinism|Calvinist]], 5.5% of no religious affiliation and 4.8% did not wish to answer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ksh.hu/apps/hntr.telepules?p_lang=EN&p_id=27881|title=Detailed Gazetteer of Hungary|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Hungarian Central Statistical Office|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=5 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Transport ==\nThe closest railway station is in [[P\u00e9cs]], 16 kilometers to the northwest. The village lies near the [[M60 motorway (Hungary)|M60]] motorway, which opened in the area in 2010 and currently provides links west to [[P\u00e9cs]] and north to [[Budapest]] (via the [[M6 motorway (Hungary)|M6 motorway]]), and will eventually provide links to the [[Croatia]]n border at [[Iv\u00e1nd\u00e1rda]] and [[Barcs]].\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://portal.ksh.hu/pls/portal/cp.hnt_telep?NN=27881 Local statistics] {{in lang|hu}}\n\n{{Baranya}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hassagy}}\n[[Category:Populated places in Baranya County]]\n\n\n{{Baranya-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/H%C3%A1ss%C3%A1gy"}
